s of family research, exile, memory, life in the ex-GDR and Strasbourg and examines Honigmann’s place within recent Jewish literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aDDR. 4aErinnerung. 4aExil. 4aHonigmann, Barbara. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aBarbara Honigmann, Exile, GDR, Memory.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2008z9783110212129oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2008z9783110209457oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978348465169240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978348497025040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783484970250423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783484970250/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGAb2008  aZDB-23-DGGb2008  aZDB-23-GTRc2000d2014